@hgrecco Ah, cool, I didn't know about [contexts](https://pint.readthedocs.io/en/0.8/contexts.html)! However, I don't know how to specify one in this case — what should I use instead of [length] and [frequency] for these fuel economy units? Or is that text arbitrary?

Generally, though, I would argue that there is a generic way: try to convert to target units, and if that fails, try the reciprocal, and if that fails, raise. Am I missing some horrible failure case?

Regarding 100km, would you say then that I should define my own unit of distance, _100km = 100km, and then let pint do its magic, probably with a context? Also, would a contribution be welcome that defined `_\d+.?\d*` as a valid modifier to any unit, meaning that number of units? I can see other uses for this, like computing 500m split times.

