With the code, you submitted 3200000 to database. pyspider need a lot of time to handle that huge number of tasks and save them into database. You can use some sub-tasks to split them into pieceses:

```
def on_start(self):
    for part in range(3200):
        self.crawl("data:,part-%d" % part, callback=self.part, save=part)

def part(self, response):
    for url_two in range(1000):
        url_two = response.save * 1000 + url_two
        self.crawl(N_Url, callback=self.json_parser, priority=9)
```

NOTE: Don't forget use `priority` to handler the real API requests in each part before move to next.

