By default, parler caches the translations into the cache (e.g. memcached). So the next time, these fields no longer have to be requested. Make sure you have your `CACHES` set to point to memcached, e.g.:

```
CACHES = {
    'default': {
        'BACKEND': 'django.core.cache.backends.memcached.MemcachedCache',
        'KEY_PREFIX': 'mysite.production',
        'LOCATION': '127.0.0.1:11211',
        'TIMEOUT': 24*3600
    },
}
```

In other situations, you can use `.prefetch_related('translations')` to prefetch all translations. Note that it will query all languages, not just your current language.

