Hi @jjoachim 

If you want to perform processing within SDK processing pipe, you can wrap your code in a processing block like this: 
```cpp
rs2::frame_queue q;
rs2::processing_block pb([](rs2::frame f, rs2::frame_source& src) {
    rs2::frame new_frame = src.allocate_video_frame(f.get_profile(), f);
    rs2::video_frame orig = f;
    auto ptr = (uint16_t*)new_frame.get_data();
    memcpy(ptr, f.get_data(), orig.get_width() * orig.get_height() * orig.get_bytes_per_pixel());
    // Put your processing code here
    src.frame_ready(new_frame);
});
pb.start(q);
```
And then invoke it, like so: 
```cpp
pb.invoke(depth);
depth = q.wait_for_frame();
```

Let me know if this helps, or if you encounter any problem

